    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Hosea",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 8,
        "summary": "Both Israel and Judah have forsaken the Lord\u2014The Lord has written the great things of His law to Ephraim.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Set the trumpet to thy mouth. He shall come as an eagle against the house of the Lord, because they have transgressed my covenant, and trespassed against my law.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0shofar, or ram's horn.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:49.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 6:7.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Israel shall cry unto me, My God, we know thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:21 (21\u201323); Luke 6:46; D&C 112:26.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Titus 1:16.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Israel hath cast off the thing that is good: the enemy shall pursue him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 17:5 (1\u20136, 24).",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They have set up kings, but not by me: they have made princes, and I knew it not: of their silver and their gold have they made them idols, that they may be cut off.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thy calf, O Samaria, hath cast thee off; mine anger is kindled against them: how long will it be ere they attain to innocency?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 12:28 (28\u201330); Acts 7:41.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0before they become clean.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For from Israel was it also: the workman made it; therefore it is not God: but the calf of Samaria shall be broken in pieces.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind: it hath no stalk: the bud shall yield no meal: if so be it yield, the strangers shall swallow it up.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 7:30; D&C 6:33.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1128
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Israel is swallowed up: now shall they be among the Gentiles as a vessel wherein is no pleasure.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 10:12; Jacob 5:13 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 31:12; Jer. 22:28; 48:38.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For they are gone up to Assyria, a wild ass alone by himself: Ephraim hath hired lovers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 15:19; 17:6 (3\u20136); Ezek. 23:5.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 16:33 (33, 41).",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, though they have hired among the nations, now will I gather them, and they shall sorrow a little for the burden of the king of princes.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Because Ephraim hath made many altars to sin, altars shall be unto him to sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 34:13; Hosea 10:1.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have written to him the great things of my law, but they were counted as a strange thing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 4:1, 6 (1\u20132, 6\u20138).",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They sacrifice flesh for the sacrifices of mine offerings, and eat it; but the Lord accepteth them not; now will he remember their iniquity, and visit their sins: they shall return to Egypt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 5:22 (21\u201322).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 8:7.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:68 (58\u201359, 68); Hosea 9:3 (1\u20133); 11:5.",
                        "start": 184,
                        "end": 189
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For Israel hath forgotten his Maker, and buildeth temples; and Judah hath multiplied fenced cities: but I will send a fire upon his cities, and it shall devour the palaces thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 17:7; 45:9.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0palaces or great buildings.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0fortified.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 25:9.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}